    "summary": "I am a trilingual Italian professional with twenty-five years of experience in the fashion industry and ten years in the U.S. and European academic systems, with advanced technical and administrative skills and a constructive approach toward innovation and entrepreneurship.\n\nI am currently employed as Head of Academic Affairs at the Amsterdam Fashion Academy in Netherlands, a high-end, international boutique academy where students get the personal, individual support and assistance they require to develop their talents to the full. \n\nProbably because of my origins, Italian academic background and my creative experience with textile and non-wearable art, I gave direction to an experimental teaching methodology, focused on a conceptual exploration of fashion design. \n\nAfter studying Fashion Design at Haute Couture Koefia Academy in Rome (Italy) and experimenting in Textile Arts and No-Wearable Art during my youth, I decided to update my formal knowledge through a Master in Public Affairs in Arts Administration. \n\nMy multidisciplinary approach led me to found STEMplusD in 2013 (with Arch. Aurorisa Mateo, dean of EIDA in PR, USA): a design concept that aims to enhance the importance of progressive integration between STEM (science, technology, engineering and mathematics) and design disciplines. Since the beginning of 2015, I\u2019ve been studying extensively the world of Fashion Technology and its relations with Wearable Technology, finally defining a new concept of integration between fashion and technology: TechCouturism.",
