            "description": "STEMplusD means Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics plus Design. The project proposes a change in common paradigm according to which design is a visual and aesthetical application on scientific and technological creations. Our idea is to place Science, Technology, Engineering, Mathematics and Design at the same level.\n\nSTEMplusD is a project by the Escuela Internacional de Dise\u00f1o y Arquitectura (EIDA) of Universidad del Turabo (Sistema Universitario Ana. G. M\u00e9ndez), Puerto Rico.\n\nCristiano Carciani is co-founder of STEMplusD.",
